RACE.FOOTNOTES: CATHERINE BLAZE trailed in the two path, moved out of last in the three path around the far turn, grinded away in the four to five path and between horses coming to midstretch, sustained progress to bid in the final sixteenth along with an outer rival and prevailed. MALIBU SMART tracked three wide, but faded in the four path approaching the far turn, regained stride in the five to six path in upper stretch, changed over at the three sixteenths pole, stayed on along with an inner rival to offer a bid in the closing stages, but came up short. REQUESTFORPROPOSAL stalked two wide and between horses down the backstretch, ranged up to bid in the three path entering the lane, sparred through upper stretch before being outkicked by an outer rival at the furlong grounds, and yielded. PROUD PERFORMER set the pace along the inside, resisted an outer challenge while entering the lane in the two path, dueled through upper stretch but yielded passing the furlong grounds. MIKITA tracked along the inside, but steadied while failing to slip inside of the early pace setter in upper stretch and faded.
